headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 38 points, including a career-high nine 3-pointers, and the Utah Jazz defeated the Detroit Pistons 126-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 38 to lead Jazz past Pistons 126-111

headlines.description: — The only yells in the Chicago locker room were happy ones.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls snap 4-game slide, top short-handed Heat 113-103

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 22 points, Jalen Brunson had 21 and the New York Knicks rolled to their eighth straight victory, beating the depleted Golden State Warriors 132-94 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rout Warriors 132-94, extend win streak to 8 games

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 29 points and the Washington Wizards stopped their 10-game losing streak on Tuesday night, beating the Phoenix Suns 113-110.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards snap losing streak at 10, beat Suns 113-110

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 13 points, 13 rebounds and 13 assists for his second straight triple-double to lead the Denver Nuggets over the Memphis Grizzlies 105-91 on Tuesday night in a matchup between the top two teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's latest triple-double leads Nuggets past Grizzlies
